Content: [telegram] <J> Atomic swap process works well, but let‚Äôs distinguish between atomic swaps and actually getting a match.  If you don‚Äôt get a marketmatch, you don‚Äôt get to experience the atomic swap.  I would also respectfully disagree that it isn‚Äôt just a matter of setting up LP and getting more bobs. That might average out to ‚Äúmore success‚Äù by sheer number of attempts, but I think beta more accurately describes where BarterDex presently is. It‚Äôs important not to delude ourselves with its performance and acknowledge its present status. Note the vast numbers of Assetchains being swapped, which is fantastic. However, barely a fraction of the atomic swaps are for any other coins. I don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs simply a matter of too few LPs, but some kinks that still need to be weeded out. I‚Äôm confident they will, but at the same time don‚Äôt want people to get the idea that it‚Äôs simply an LP numbers thing and then be disappointed when it doesn‚Äôt improve as much as expected.
